{"TopicId":148567,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How to make a 6 satellite geostationary network.","CreatedByName":"Dfthu","CreatedById":80296,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-24T18:21:34Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Dfthu","CreatedById":80296,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-24T18:21:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I built a\u00A0rocket that has 6 satellites and I need to make a\u00A0geostationary network. How do I get them evenly spaced out?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rodhern","CreatedById":144074,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-24T18:26:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are some more advanced recipes posted here and there. I am a bit primitive, I would just make the orbit a little \u0027too\u0027 low initially, that way they will be advancing ever more east. Then as each one get in position I would raise their orbit to Keostationary.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: Btw. if you don\u0027t have a reason the satellites should be keostationary in the first place, almost any network with equatorial orbits of the same radius for all six satellites work just fine (communication network wise).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-24T18:29:33Z\u0022 title=\u002209/24/2016 06:29  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 24, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Rodhern\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eadded comment\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dfthu","CreatedById":80296,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-24T18:27:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Yea I know you\u00A0have do that, I just wanted to know how low do I go.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rodhern","CreatedById":144074,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-24T18:32:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAhh. Sorry I cant help you. One rule of course is to get close enough that you don\u0027t overshoot the target position in the final orbit before the final adjustment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ycen","CreatedById":169118,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-25T06:10:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Here is a tool is used allot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://kerbility.com/calc/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://kerbility.com/calc/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:16px/24px \u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;color:rgb(17,17,17);text-transform:none;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(253,253,253);\u0022\u003ESo for 6 sats youre orbit should look like a oval.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0 3.613.030\u003Cbr\u003E\nPer 2.863.334\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:16px/24px \u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;color:rgb(17,17,17);text-transform:none;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(253,253,253);\u0022\u003EDrop them at PER.\u00A0!!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:16px/24px \u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;color:rgb(17,17,17);text-transform:none;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(253,253,253);\u0022\u003EEach sat need about 50dv to slow down.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:16px/24px \u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;color:rgb(17,17,17);text-transform:none;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(253,253,253);\u0022\u003EThe Geo Orbit is \u003Cstrong\u003Enot\u003C/strong\u003E 6\u00A0hrs. \u003Cstrong\u003EBut\u003C/strong\u003E 5hr 59min 9.4sec\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:16px/24px \u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;color:rgb(17,17,17);text-transform:none;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(253,253,253);\u0022\u003E\u00A0(just so you know)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:16px/24px \u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;color:rgb(17,17,17);text-transform:none;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(253,253,253);\u0022\u003ECheers!!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Van Disaster","CreatedById":58876,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-25T06:17:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou put your carrier craft in a resonant orbit - I\u0027d imagine 1/6 would be fine for geosync, although if you\u0027d rather use more fuel on the carrier than the sats you can use a bigger resonant orbit \u0026amp; reorient the carrier after every couple of launches. At each \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E you throw a sat out \u0026amp; circularize it ( edit - actually it doesn\u0027t really matter when you throw them out, you could just chuck them all out at once and then they\u0027re *all* in a resonant orbit ).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn RT the best coverage is provided by two pairs of low-level sats in polar orbits ( and I usually throw one relay in geosync over \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E ), I\u0027m presuming it\u0027s not that way in stock?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n( geosync for kerbin is probably kerbosync or maybe kerbinsync, keosync is meaningless \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E )\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-25T06:33:22Z\u0022 title=\u002209/25/2016 06:33  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Van Disaster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dfthu","CreatedById":80296,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-25T06:18:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222773229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148567\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474783838\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022169118\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ycen\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, ycen said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Here is a tool is used allot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://kerbility.com/calc/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://kerbility.com/calc/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:16px/24px \u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;color:rgb(17,17,17);text-transform:none;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(253,253,253);\u0022\u003ESo for 6 sats youre orbit should look like a oval.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0 3.613.030\u003Cbr\u003E\nPer 2.863.334\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:16px/24px \u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;color:rgb(17,17,17);text-transform:none;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(253,253,253);\u0022\u003EDrop them at PER.\u00A0!!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:16px/24px \u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;color:rgb(17,17,17);text-transform:none;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(253,253,253);\u0022\u003EEach sat need about 50dv to slow down.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:16px/24px \u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;color:rgb(17,17,17);text-transform:none;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(253,253,253);\u0022\u003EThe Geo Orbit is \u003Cstrong\u003Enot\u003C/strong\u003E 6\u00A0hrs. \u003Cstrong\u003EBut\u003C/strong\u003E 5hr 59min 9.4sec\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:16px/24px \u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;color:rgb(17,17,17);text-transform:none;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(253,253,253);\u0022\u003E\u00A0(just so you know)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:16px/24px \u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;color:rgb(17,17,17);text-transform:none;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(253,253,253);\u0022\u003ECheers!!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell thank you\u00A0but.... I already did it. I went on the IRC chat and they told me to use this \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.adammil.net/tmp/sats.htm.,\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.adammil.net/tmp/sats.htm.,\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0and it worked fine. I don\u0027t how to answer./close this topic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222773236\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148567\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474784277\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Van Disaster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Van Disaster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou put your carrier craft in a resonant orbit - I\u0027d imagine 1/6 would be fine for geosync. At each \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E you throw a sat out \u0026amp; circularize it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn RT the best coverage is provided by two pairs of low-level sats in polar orbits ( and I usually throw one relay in geosync over \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E ), I\u0027m presuming it\u0027s not that way in stock?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n( geosync for kerbin is probably kerbosync or maybe kerbinsync, keosync is meaningless \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E )\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried 1/6 of geo and it didn\u0027t work. The orbits were way outa wack.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Higgs","CreatedById":121852,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-25T07:07:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/80296-dfthu/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002280296\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/80296-dfthu/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dfthu\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0if you ask for a moderator to close the thread usually by naming one like vanamonde or whomever with an \u003Cspan\u003E@ and his/her name they usually will oblige you with a closure. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dfthu","CreatedById":80296,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-25T07:08:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222773266\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148567\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474787221\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022121852\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Higgs\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Higgs said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/80296-dfthu/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002280296\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/80296-dfthu/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dfthu\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0if you ask for a moderator to close the thread usually by naming one like vanamonde or whomever with an \u003Cspan\u003E@ and his/her name they usually will oblige you with a closure. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, I chose a best answer and it shows a checkmark on the page so it should be fine\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003